  "course_description": "The neurobiology of sexual desire, hunger, thirst, arousal, drug addiction, and sleeping and waking.",
  "course_notes": "(No freshmen allowed to register in this class.) (Prior completion of PSYC 110 or PSYC 111, or AP/IB credit in psychology.) (The goal of this course is to explore how the brain gives rise to behavior. Topics include the nervous system, neuroplasticity, sensory and motor systems, attention, memory, sleep, emotion, motivation, social cognition, and brain and behavioral disorders.)",
